Going to see Doctor Strange. Haven’t seen any reviews or spoilers. I am hoping to be wowed. This is ambitious movie about truly putting Dr Strange in the upper echelon of the Avengers in terms of popularity and story.

(1/4) Just finished the new Doctor Strange movie, & it was crazy good! Raimi’s horror-like directing paired with some of the hokeyness of the MCU made for a weird yet totally captivating experience that I loved! Definitely think this is a movie that will get even better with age.

(2/4) I really appreciated how contained the story felt. There were tons of cameos & callbacks but recognizing them all wasn’t what drove the fun or story. If a reference was necessary, it was explained, but the excitement came from all the cool new stuff that was happening now.

(3/4) The MCU cross-references do a great job at getting me to theaters, but I think I best enjoy a film when its most interesting moments aren’t just pointers to previous installments. In this regard, I think DS2 does a good job at standing out in the modern Marvel lineup.
